HONG KONG
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
This painting is part of the Frye Art Museum's collection in Seattle, Washington.
HONG KONG Harbor is one of the busiest in all Asia. It bustles with ferries... carying half a million
passengers a day...and freighters and endless junks and sampans. At Aberdeen, you will find a
whole village of people who live all their lives on boats. Across the harbor in Kowloon, shops and
stalls bulge with merchandise as shoppers bargain noisily. The Furama Inter-Continental is centrally
located and provides a wide range of amenities. Pan Am serves Hong Kong every day on its
Round-The-World flights, from New York via Tokyo and nonstop from San Francisco.
